_______________________
I may be missing only 4 or 5 volumes, but pretty much all sets are complete.

THIS IS NOT SCATTERED JUNK. 

If you've been in a record pool or purchased a remix service 12'' then you know each vol. is worth $8-12 each and your getting over 100 volumes! Do the math. I spent over $5000 USD on these sets...for the vinyl + record pool fees... plus the time it takes to convert them from 12'' to mp3. Bpm tagged and ready to go.

Downloading crap from the internet...limewire, kazaa, etc? That crap has no proper bar count so you CANT MIX properly. Other Djs can tell when your mixing instrumentals just to get by. Not to mention the horrible 128kbps quality you get when you download your music off the internet. Yes on professional PA systems you can actually hear the bad quality. My files are 192-320kbps.

Keep your compilations backed up in mint condition! Regardless what you do, vinyl will go bad even if taken care of.

Heat, overuse in same area play a big factor. Respect your artists and labels. Use your own discretion, anything you do not own on vinyl/cd, discard within 24hrs, these are meant only as back ups to what you own. All rights reserved by original labels.

No sales pitch bs hype . ___________________________________________________ 
If you have them already and was in the same record pools from back then, it will take you at least 7-12 months to convert, maybe more or less depending on how many you convert per day and how much patience you have I guess.

name: 6800+ VA Promo - Music Videos (no logo) bonus 3,000 vids
description:
OVER 6500+ NO LOGO Music Videos + bonus 3000 videos!
150 dvds remastered!
Some even have intro outro for flawless mixing! Ask for track list & video samples!!! Close to 10,000 videos total.

Videos work with: serato video sl,sl1,sl3,DVJx1, dvj1000 OR djm 800 using the proper setup.
Complete compatibility & supported hardware/software are listed at very bottom of page!

If you need help with what hardware/software is required to mix video feel free to ask. I'll help you out.

The external alone costs me $100+
NO LOW BALLERS PERIOD!

 
  That's 0.03 cents per video. No time consuming ripping needed. Works with Virtual vinyl Serato video SL and many video setups! 
Most VJ pools charge $200-500 per year ($30-$60) per month. I have collected these videos for the last decade, 
save thousands on annual fees.


Not sure this will work on your VDJ setup??  Pls ask for video samples & list BEFORE you buy!
Also Pls state your email & current hardware/software setup.

 
These are not downloaded junk videos. These were remastered for video Djs in high quality audio/video. 
Some even contain intro /outro for flawless mixing. Videos are up to date w/ latest Top 40. Also has Reggae, Dance, Rnb, Alt, Rock, 70s, 80s and even 90's classics and tons more...All Genres covered 


- Free 750gb external hard drive! Yours to keep! - 


Promo originals with no logos, NOT bootlegs.
All high quality videos!

Perfect for video DJ's.
I've had the opportunity to work with many Producers/DJs/Artists while working in the music industry as a full time DJ and part time record distributor for many famous record labels.



Mixing plain old music is dead...The era of the VIDEO DJ is here!
Not only is it more fun and gets the crowd more hype then the old fashion DJ, but they wont be staring at you all day.....they will be focused on your video mixing. There's nothing  like mixing a music video while manipulating the picture and you are able to visually see yourself scratching & mixing.



________________________________________

Compatibility: 
Important pls read!!!

Rane TTM57, Serato SL1-SL3 & Video SL users:
TTM57 & video SL users.
Videos tested and approved. Mac & PC OK! 

Virtual Vinyl, Virtual DJ, & Cue 6.0.3 users:
Videos tested and approved. Mac & PC OK!
Virtual vinyl/Virtual DJ....is the most stable setup I use.
Has given me less problems then video sl. It also supports almost all video format, divx, avi, mpeg, mp4, and even VOB.
Other supported hardware using Virtual DJ software: Hercules RMX, Hercules Steel, Denon DN-S3700 & CDJ-400.
Other supported hardware using Cue 6.0.3 software: NS7, TOTAL CONTROL, STEALTH CONTROL, OMNI CONTROL, iCDX, M1USB, C3USB, X1USB, DJ|iO & VIRTUAL VINYL.


DVJ1000 & X1users:
Users have to create a DVD cd with the videos using a DVD authoring software.
Since DVJ only reads DVD finalized cds and not video data (mpeg1,2,mp4,avi/divx etc.)
I have spoke with Pioneer tech support, they have suggested to use "DVD Architect" by Sony with my videos.

Traktor, Torq, or Final scratch? If you use these setups pls check if it can support video.
I have not been keeping up to date with these since I do not use them. 

If you need a track list pls message me with an email.


Returns & Refunds Policy:
Since we offer video samples to ensure quality, 
customer expectations, hardware software compatibility & a detailed list
there will be absolutely NO RETURNS or REFUNDS.
